d world champions, who began a sit-in protest on a pavement near the Indian Parliament in New Delhi in January last year, demanding that Singh be sacked from the WFI and investigated over allegations that he had sexually harassed female wrestlers since 2012.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999971157996681, \"rank\": 1.7750558512692222e-06, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 2278, \"end\": 2287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"score\": 0.996744774896897, \"rank\": 0.0032658291296013106, \"text\": \"New Delhi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His words\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2113}, {\"ngram\": \"world champions\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"a sit-in protest\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"a pavement\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"the Indian Parliament\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"Singh\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"the WFI\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2387}, {\"ngram\": \"female wrestlers\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were led by three elite athletes - Vinesh Phogat, considered India's most successful woman wrestler with three consecutive gold medals at the Commonwealth Games; Bajrang Punia, a bronze medallist at the Tokyo Olympics 2020; and Sakshi Malik, the first Indian female wrestler to win an Olympic medal, in Rio de Janeiro in 2016.\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou