\"Set up by Usha Sihag, India's first woman wrestling coach, and her husband Sanjay Sihag, the academy lies at the end of a large plot of land that houses a school.\", \"from\": 13130, \"to\": 13292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13140, \"end\": 13144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ushas\", \"score\": 0.9782518860551752, \"rank\": 0.022183499284054876, \"text\": \"Usha\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ushas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ushas\"}, {\"begin\": 13152, \"end\": 13157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999992729386037, \"rank\": 6.123566169388104e-07, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 13205, \"end\": 13211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\", \"score\": 0.9142273677569516, \"rank\": 0.054559586827990406, \"text\": \"Sanjay\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her husband\", \"from\": 13193, \"to\": 13204}, {\"ngram\": \"the academy\", \"from\": 13219, \"to\": 13230}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 13239, \"to\": 13246}, {\"ngram\": \"a large plot\", \"from\": 13250, \"to\": 13262}, {\"ngram\": \"land\", \"from\": 13266, \"to\": 13270}, {\"ngram\": \"a school\", \"from\": 13283, \"to\": 13291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Split into two, on the left is a long wrestling hall.\", \"from\": 13294, \"to\": 13347, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 13313, \"to\": 13321}, {\"ngram\": \"a long wrestling hall\", \"from\": 13325, \"to\": 13346}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Constructed like a modern industrial shed, it has a square blue mat - 12 by 12 metres - and some gym equipment around it.\", \"from\": 13348, \"to\": 13469, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a modern industrial shed\", \"from\": 13365, \"to\": 13389}, {\"ngram\": \"a square blue mat\", \"from\": 13398, \"to\": 13415}, {\"ngram\": \"12 metres\", \"from\": 13424, \"to\": 13433}, {\"ngram\": \"some gym equipment\", \"from\": 13440, \"to\": 13458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Running parallel to it, across a muddy patch of land with shrubs, is a row of rooms bookended by a kitchen and dining area in the front, and bathrooms at the other.\", \"from\": 13471, \"to\": 13635, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a muddy patch\", \"from\": 13502, \"to\": 13515}, {\"ngram\": \"land\", \"from\": 13519, \"to\": 13523}, {\"ngram\": \"shrubs\", \"from\": 13529, \"to\": 13535}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 13540, \"to\": 13545}, {\"ngram\": \"rooms\", \"from\": 13549, \"to\": 13554}, {\"ngram\": \"a kitchen and dining area\", \"from\": 13568, \"to\": 13593}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 13597, \"to\": 13606}, {\"ngram\": \"bathrooms\", \"from\": 13612, \"to\": 13621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In these seven hostel rooms with mesh doors and folding beds stacked together, idols of Hindu gods rest on top of steel almirahs, medals hang from nails in walls and alarm clocks are set at 4am.\", \"from\": 13636, \"to\": 13830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13724, \"end\": 13729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindus\", \"score\": 0.9962610813514722, \"rank\": 0.003695539499963471, \"text\": \"Hindu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these seven hostel rooms\", \"from\": 13639, \"to\": 13663}, {\"ngram\": \"mesh doors\", \"from\": 13669, \"to\": 13679}, {\"ngram\": \"folding beds\", \"from\": 13684, \"to\": 13696}, {\"ngram\": \"idols\", \"from\": 13715, \"to\": 13720}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 13743, \"to\": 13746}, {\"ngram\": \"steel almirahs\", \"from\": 13750, \"to\": 13764}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 13766, \"to\": 13772}, {\"ngram\": \"nails\", \"from\": 13783, \"to\": 13788}, {\"ngram\": \"walls\", \"from\": 13792, \"to\": 13797}, {\"ngram\": \"alarm clocks\", \"from\": 13802, \"to\": 13814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Monday to Saturday, at 5am, the wrestlers begin their routine with a jog around the playground.\", \"from\": 13832, \"to\": 13927, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 13842, \"to\": 13850}, {\"ngram\": \"the wrestlers\", \"from\": 13860, \"to\": 13873}, {\"ngram\": \"their routine\", \"from\": 13880, \"to\": 13893}, {\"ngram\": \"a jog\", \"from\": 13899, \"to\": 13904}, {\"ngram\": \"the playground\", \"from\": 13912, \"to\": 13926}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the moody blue sky, they look like silent shadows bobbing up and down.\", \"from\": 13928, \"to\": 14004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moody blue sky\", \"from\": 13934, \"to\": 13952}, {\"ngram\": \"silent shadows\", \"from\": 13969, \"to\": 13983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's endurance one day, strength training another, and some days they play a game,\\\" says Naveen, 28.\", \"from\": 14006, \"to\": 14107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14096, \"end\": 14102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naveen_Patnaik\", \"score\": 0.9917667914940759, \"rank\": 0.008301556562362252, \"text\": \"Naveen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naveen_Patnaik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naveen_Patnaik\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"endurance\", \"from\": 14012, \"to\": 14021}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 14049, \"to\": 14056}, {\"ngram\": \"a game\", \"from\": 14082, \"to\": 14088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A petite former wrestler in running shorts, her long hair tied in a top knot and a whistle around her neck, she conducts the morning workout sessions and is the hostel warden.\", \"from\": 14108, \"to\": 14283, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"running shorts\", \"from\": 14136, \"to\": 14150}, {\"ngram\": \"her long hair\", \"from\": 14152, \"to\": 14165}, {\"ngram\": \"a top knot\", \"from\": 14174, \"to\": 14184}, {\"ngram\": \"a whistle\", \"from\": 14189, \"to\": 14198}, {\"ngram\": \"her neck\", \"from\": 14206, \"to\": 14214}, {\"ngram\": \"the morning workout sessions\", \"from\": 14229, \"to\": 14257}, {\"ngram\": \"the hostel warden\", \"from\": 14265, \"to\": 14282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Altius - taken from the Olympic motto, Citius, Altius, Fortius (Faster, Higher, Stronger) - is a girls-only academy, but \\\"Coach Saab\\\", as Sanjay is called, recently gave in to parents' requests to take in the younger brothers of girls who had been admitted.\", \"from\": 14285, \"to\": 14542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14324, \"end\": 14347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Citius, Altius, Fortius\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\"}, {\"begin\": 14324, \"end\": 14347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Citius, Altius, Fortius\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\"}, {\"begin\": 14413, \"end\": 14417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saab_Automobile\", \"score\": 0.9994910721500124, \"rank\": 0.00041062920825544525, \"text\": \"Saab\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saab_Automobile\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saab_Automobile\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Altius\", \"from\": 14285, \"to\": 14291}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic motto\", \"from\": 14305, \"to\": 14322}, {\"ngram\": \"a girls-only academy\", \"from\": 14380, \"to\": 14400}, {\"ngram\": \"Sanjay\", \"from\": 14423, \"to\": 14429}, {\"ngram\": \"parents' requests\", \"from\": 14461, \"to\": 14478}, {\"ngram\": \"the younger brothers\", \"from\": 14490, \"to\": 14510}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 14514, \"to\": 14519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its 28 aspiring wrestlers, from ages 7 to 19, are a mix of cute boys with long eyelashes and pink lips; muscular, butch girls with crewcuts; and Lakshita, 11.\", \"from\": 14543, \"to\": 14701, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its 28 aspiring wrestlers\", \"from\": 14543, \"to\": 14568}, {\"ngram\": \"ages\", \"from\": 14575, \"to\": 14579}, {\"ngram\": \"a mix\", \"from\": 14593, \"to\": 14598}, {\"ngram\": \"cute boys\", \"from\": 14602, \"to\": 14611}, {\"ngram\": \"long eyelashes\", \"from\": 14617, \"to\": 14631}, {\"ngram\": \"pink lips\", \"from\": 14636, \"to\": 14645}, {\"ngram\": \"muscular, butch girls\", \"from\": 14647, \"to\": 14668}, {\"ngram\": \"crewcuts\", \"from\": 14674, \"to\": 14682}, {\"ngram\": \"Lakshita\", \"from\": 14688, \"to\": 14696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike others, Lakshita is not in sports gear.\", \"from\": 14703, \"to\": 14749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 14710, \"to\": 14716}, {\"ngram\": \"Lakshita\", \"from\": 14718, \"to\": 14726}, {\"ngram\": \"sports gear\", \"from\": 14737, \"to\": 14748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her black sweatshirt is embellished with shiny, big pearls, and in front are two furry, pink swans facing each other, forming a heart.\", \"from\": 14750, \"to\": 14884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her black sweatshirt\", \"from\": 14750, \"to\": 14770}, {\"ngram\": \"shiny, big pearls\", \"from\": 14791, \"to\": 14808}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 14817, \"to\": 14822}, {\"ngram\": \"two furry, pink swans\", \"from\": 14827, \"to\": 14848}, {\"ngram\": \"a heart\", \"from\": 14876, \"to\": 14883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She saunters in a different direction from others, and sometimes she leans on a pillar to watch.\", \"from\": 14885, \"to\": 14981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a different direction\", \"from\": 14901, \"to\": 14922}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 14928, \"to\": 14934}, {\"ngram\": \"a pillar\", \"from\": 14963, \"to\": 14971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She is special, but very bright,\\\" says Sanjay, 47, who arrives at the academy in the evenings, after his day job in Haryana's education department, to conduct wrestling practice.\", \"from\": 14983, \"to\": 15162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15100, \"end\": 15107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"score\": 0.9998887938663543, \"rank\": 6.794371798658751e-05, \"text\": \"Haryana\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sanjay\", \"from\": 15023, \"to\": 15029}, {\"ngram\": \"the academy\", \"from\": 15050, \"to\": 15061}, {\"ngram\": \"the evenings\", \"from\": 15065, \"to\": 15077}, {\"ngram\": \"his day job\", \"from\": 15085, \"to\": 15096}, {\"ngram\": \"wrestling practice\", \"from\": 15143, \"to\": 15161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clean shaven, with traces of grey in his hair, Sanjay is stern on the mat, but affectionate off it, with a ready smile.\", \"from\": 15164, \"to\": 15283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15211, \"end\": 15217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\", \"score\": 0.5518045229571514, \"rank\": 0.7517508551709039, \"text\": \"Sanjay\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"traces\", \"from\": 15183, \"to\": 15189}, {\"ngram\": \"grey\", \"from\": 15193, \"to\": 15197}, {\"ngram\": \"his hair\", \"from\": 15201, \"to\": 15209}, {\"ngram\": \"the mat\", \"from\": 15230, \"to\": 15237}, {\"ngram\": \"a ready smile\", \"from\": 15269, \"to\": 15282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parents of his students refer to him as \\\"Bhagwan\\\" (God) - in deference to a teacher, but also because they are grateful that he never pesters them when fees are delayed.\", \"from\": 15284, \"to\": 15453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Parents\", \"from\": 15284, \"to\": 15291}, {\"ngram\": \"his students\", \"from\": 15295, \"to\": 15307}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Bhagwan\", \"from\": 15324, \"to\": 15332}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 15335, \"to\": 15338}, {\"ngram\": \"deference\", \"from\": 15345, \"to\": 15354}, {\"ngram\": \"a teacher\", \"from\": 15358, \"to\": 15367}, {\"ngram\": \"fees\", \"from\": 15436, \"to\": 15440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Since all her siblings are here, Lakshita's parents did not want her to be alone at home.\", \"from\": 15455, \"to\": 15545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all her siblings\", \"from\": 15462, \"to\": 15478}, {\"ngram\": \"Lakshita's parents\", \"from\": 15489, \"to\": 15507}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 15540, \"to\": 15544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She will not become a player,\\\" he says.\", \"from\": 15546, \"to\": 15585, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a player\", \"from\": 15566, \"to\": 15574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But she participates in the morning exercises, the evening mat practice, and is learning life skills.\\\"\", \"from\": 15586, \"to\": 15689, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the morning exercises\", \"from\": 15611, \"to\": 15632}, {\"ngram\": \"the evening mat practice\", \"from\": 15634, \"to\": 15658}, {\"ngram\": \"life skills\", \"from\": 15676, \"to\": 15687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most wrestling academies in Haryana, especially those for women, are safe, familial spaces where parents leave their young daughters and sons in the care of coaches they trust.\", \"from\": 15691, \"to\": 15867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15719, \"end\": 15726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"score\": 0.9999999912342901, \"rank\": 5.7057577740757366e-09, \"text\": \"Haryana\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most wrestling academies\", \"from\": 15691, \"to\": 15715}, {\"ngram\": \"especially those\", \"from\": 15728, \"to\": 15744}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 15749, \"to\": 15754}, {\"ngram\": \"safe, familial spaces\", \"from\": 15760, \"to\": 15781}, {\"ngram\": \"parents\", \"from\": 15788, \"to\": 15795}, {\"ngram\": \"their young daughters\", \"from\": 15802, \"to\": 15823}, {\"ngram\": \"sons\", \"from\": 15828, \"to\": 15832}, {\"ngram\": \"the care\", \"from\": 15836, \"to\": 15844}, {\"ngram\": \"coaches\", \"from\": 15848, \"to\": 15855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until January last year, many parents believed that the broader wrestling universe, too, was an extension of these cosy, neighbourly spaces.\", \"from\": 15868, \"to\": 16008, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 15874, \"to\": 15881}, {\"ngram\": \"many parents\", \"from\": 15893, \"to\": 15905}, {\"ngram\": \"the broader wrestling universe\", \"from\": 15920, \"to\": 15950}, {\"ngram\": \"an extension\", \"from\": 15961, \"to\": 15973}, {\"ngram\": \"these cosy, neighbourly spaces\", \"from\": 15977, \"to\": 16007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sport is the 37th caste in Haryana,\\\" says Sanjay, referring to the state's 36 caste-based clans that follow a common patriarchal code and share their love for kushti, as wrestling is known in these parts.\", \"from\": 16010, \"to\": 16215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16038, \"end\": 16045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"score\": 0.9999999912342901, \"rank\": 5.7057577740757366e-09, \"text\": \"Haryana\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\"}, {\"begin\": 16053, \"end\": 16059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\", \"score\": 0.5518045229571514, \"rank\": 0.7517508551709039, \"text\": \"Sanjay\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sanjay_Gandhi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 16011, \"to\": 16016}, {\"ngram\": \"the 37th caste\", \"from\": 16020, \"to\": 16034}, {\"ngram\": \"the state's 36 caste-based clans\", \"from\": 16074, \"to\": 16106}, {\"ngram\": \"a common patriarchal code\", \"from\": 16119, \"to\": 16144}, {\"ngram\": \"their love\", \"from\": 16155, \"to\": 16165}, {\"ngram\": \"kushti\", \"from\": 16170, \"to\": 16176}, {\"ngram\": \"wrestling\", \"from\": 16181, \"to\": 16190}, {\"ngram\": \"these parts\", \"from\": 16203, \"to\": 16214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dangals (wrestling tournaments held in villages) have been a part of the state's culture for ages.\", \"from\": 16217, \"to\": 16315, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dangals\", \"from\": 16217, \"to\": 16224}, {\"ngram\": \"wrestling tournaments\", \"from\": 16226, \"to\": 16247}, {\"ngram\": \"villages\", \"from\": 16256, \"to\": 16264}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 16276, \"to\": 16282}, {\"ngram\": \"the state's culture\", \"from\": 16286, \"to\": 16305}, {\"ngram\": \"ages\", \"from\": 16310, \"to\": 16314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most villages have an akhara - traditional wrestling academies with boarding, lodging and mud pits - that, until the late 1990s, were men-only spaces where burly wrestlers in loincloths prayed to the celibate Hindu god Hanuman, slapped their oiled thighs and vied for titles like Rustam-e-Hind and Hind Kesari.\", \"from\": 16316, \"to\": 16626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16525, \"end\": 16530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindus\", \"score\": 0.9954460913104191, \"rank\": 0.004574700948175084, \"text\": \"Hindu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindus\"}, {\"begin\": 16535, \"end\": 16542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanuman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0201627836195087e-26, \"text\": \"Hanuman\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanuman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanuman\"}, {\"begin\": 16596, \"end\": 16609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Great_Gama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rustam-e-Hind\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Great_Gama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Great_Gama\"}, {\"begin\": 16614, \"end\": 16625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hind_Kesari\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5232970370059883e-35, \"text\": \"Hind Kesari\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hind_Kesari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hind_Kesari\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most villages\", \"from\": 16316, \"to\": 16329}, {\"ngram\": \"an akhara - traditional wrestling academies\", \"from\": 16335, \"to\": 16378}, {\"ngram\": \"boarding, lodging and mud pits\", \"from\": 16384, \"to\": 16414}, {\"ngram\": \"the late 1990s\", \"from\": 16429, \"to\": 16443}, {\"ngram\": \"men-only spaces\", \"from\": 16450, \"to\": 16465}, {\"ngram\": \"burly wrestlers\", \"from\": 16472, \"to\": 16487}, {\"ngram\": \"loincloths\", \"from\": 16491, \"to\": 16501}, {\"ngram\": \"their oiled thighs\", \"from\": 16552, \"to\": 16570}, {\"ngram\": \"titles\", \"from\": 16584, \"to\": 16590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first father-daughter team to knock on this male bastion was Master Chandgi Ram, a wrestling legend and coach, who started training his two daughters in 1997 and taking them to dangals.\", \"from\": 16628, \"to\": 16817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16700, \"end\": 16711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandgi_Ram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chandgi Ram\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandgi_Ram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandgi_Ram\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first father-daughter team\", \"from\": 16628, \"to\": 16658}, {\"ngram\": \"this male bastion\", \"from\": 16671, \"to\": 16688}, {\"ngram\": \"a wrestling legend\", \"from\": 16713, \"to\": 16731}, {\"ngram\": \"coach\", \"from\": 16736, \"to\": 16741}, {\"ngram\": \"his two daughters\", \"from\": 16764, \"to\": 16781}, {\"ngram\": \"dangals\", \"from\": 16809, \"to\": 16816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His student, Mahavir Phogat, carried on the tradition by training his four daughters and two nieces.\", \"from\": 16819, \"to\": 16919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16832, \"end\": 16839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mahavir\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira\"}, {\"begin\": 16840, \"end\": 16846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phogat_sisters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phogat\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phogat_sisters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phogat_sisters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His student\", \"from\": 16819, \"to\": 16830}, {\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 16859, \"to\": 16872}, {\"ngram\": \"his four daughters\", \"from\": 16885, \"to\": 16903}, {\"ngram\": \"two nieces\", \"from\": 16908, \"to\": 16918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2010, six years after women's wrestling made its Olympic debut in Athens in 2004, Mahavir's eldest daughter, Geeta, became the first Indian female wrestler to qualify for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 16920, \"to\": 17107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16989, \"end\": 16995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7448827129749898, \"rank\": 0.3424929519390795, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 17005, \"end\": 17012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mahavir\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahavira\"}, {\"begin\": 17056, \"end\": 17062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9963735307784112, \"rank\": 0.0036396211654551483, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women's wrestling\", \"from\": 16945, \"to\": 16962}, {\"ngram\": \"its Olympic debut\", \"from\": 16968, \"to\": 16985}, {\"ngram\": \"Geeta\", \"from\": 17032, \"to\": 17037}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 17094, \"to\": 17106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a state where girls, considered a lifelong liability, were often eliminated in the womb, and those who were born were at times christened Kafi (enough), Maafi (forgive) or Batheri (too much), attitudes began to change.\", \"from\": 17109, \"to\": 17330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17250, \"end\": 17254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kafi\", \"score\": 0.9999999999198508, \"rank\": 6.401214324402323e-11, \"text\": \"Kafi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kafi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kafi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a state\", \"from\": 17112, \"to\": 17119}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 17126, \"to\": 17131}, {\"ngram\": \"a lifelong liability\", \"from\": 17144, \"to\": 17164}, {\"ngram\": \"the womb\", \"from\": 17191, \"to\": 17199}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 17233, \"to\": 17238}, {\"ngram\": \"Maafi\", \"from\": 17265, \"to\": 17270}, {\"ngram\": \"(forgive\", \"from\": 17271, \"to\": 17279}, {\"ngram\": \"Batheri\", \"from\": 17284, \"to\": 17291}, {\"ngram\": \"attitudes\", \"from\": 17304, \"to\": 17313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the year that really catapulted women's wrestling into the nation's consciousness and changed the relationship of Haryana's men with their daughters was 2016.\", \"from\": 17332, \"to\": 17494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17450, \"end\": 17457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.464564822247739e-16, \"text\": \"Haryana\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haryana\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 17336, \"to\": 17344}, {\"ngram\": \"women's wrestling\", \"from\": 17368, \"to\": 17385}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation's consciousness\", \"from\": 17391, \"to\": 17417}, {\"ngram\": \"the relationship\", \"from\": 17430, \"to\": 17446}, {\"ngram\": \"their daughters\", \"from\": 17469, \"to\": 17484}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That year, Sakshi Malik, the daughter of a bus conductor, became India's first female wrestler to win an Olympic medal at Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 17496, \"to\": 17633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17507, \"end\": 17519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sakshi_Malik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2015520608887241e-28, \"text\": \"Sakshi Malik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sakshi_Malik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sakshi_Malik\"}, {\"begin\": 17561, \"end\": 17566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999996374688838, \"rank\": 3.528818050624477e-07, \"text\": \"India\",